   - The main reason for the performance differences lies in the fact that the v2 model was **trained on v2 data**, while the more recent data (v3) reflects updated patterns, trends, and distributions. Since the model trained on v2 data is not adapted to the new data's characteristics, it produces inaccurate predictions.
